org.jetel.util

Class HashCodeUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.util.HashCodeUtil

  • public final class HashCodeUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    Collected methods which allow easy implementation of hashCode. All Clover's data field types - implementations, use getHash() implementations from this class; Example use case: 
     public int hashCode() {
        int result = HashCodeUtil.SEED;
        // collect the contributions of various fields
        result = HashCodeUtil.hash(result, fPrimitive);
        result = HashCodeUtil.hash(result, fObject);
        result = HashCodeUtil.hash(result, fArray);
        return result;
 }
    See Also:
    http://www.javapractices.com/topic/TopicAction.do?Id=28

      • SEED

        public static final int SEED
        An initial value for a hashCode, to which is added contributions from fields. Using a non-zero value decreases collisons of hashCode values.
